&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LTS&lt;/strong&gt; is seeking a motivated and experienced &lt;strong&gt;Agile Developer&lt;/strong&gt; to support a major modernization initiative within the Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) health portfolio. This role will contribute to the modernization of mission-critical healthcare applications and enterprise systems supporting Veteran care, including efforts related to legacy VistA/MUMPS environments, enterprise integrations, cloud modernization, and next-generation digital health solutions.&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate will thrive in a fast-paced Agile environment and possess strong full-stack or backend development experience supporting large-scale federal or healthcare IT systems. This individual will work closely with product owners, architects, engineers, and DevSecOps teams to deliver scalable, secure, and high-performing applications supporting VA modernization objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Design, develop, test, and maintain enterprise applications supporting VA healthcare modernization initiatives.&lt;br&gt;• Participate in Agile Scrum ceremonies including sprint planning, backlog refinement, daily standups, retrospectives, and demos.&lt;br&gt;• Develop and enhance applications integrating with legacy and modern healthcare systems.&lt;br&gt;• Support modernization efforts involving legacy VistA/MUMPS-based environments and enterprise integration platforms.&lt;br&gt;• Build scalable APIs, microservices, and application components using modern development frameworks and tools.&lt;br&gt;• Collaborate with architects, analysts, QA teams, and infrastructure engineers to deliver secure and reliable solutions.&lt;br&gt;• Contribute to CI/CD pipelines, DevSecOps processes, and automated testing initiatives.&lt;br&gt;• Troubleshoot and resolve application defects, performance issues, and integration challenges.&lt;br&gt;• Develop technical documentation including user stories, technical specifications, code documentation, and release notes.&lt;br&gt;• Ensure solutions align with federal cybersecurity, accessibility, and compliance requirements.&lt;br&gt;• Support continuous improvement initiatives focused on modernization, automation, and operational efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, or related discipline.&lt;br&gt;• 5+ years of software development experience in Agile environments.&lt;br&gt;• Experience developing enterprise applications using modern programming languages such as Java, C#, JavaScript, Python, or similar technologies.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with web services, APIs, and application integration technologies.&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with Agile frameworks including Scrum or Kanban.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with version control systems such as Git.&lt;br&gt;• Experience supporting CI/CD pipelines and DevSecOps practices.&lt;br&gt;• Understanding of secure coding standards and federal cybersecurity requirements.&lt;br&gt;• Strong analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;• Excellent communication and collaboration abilities within cross-functional teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to Have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Experience supporting VA healthcare systems, VistA, CPRS, or healthcare IT modernization programs.&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with MUMPS-based applications or legacy modernization initiatives.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with cloud-native development in AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud environments.&lt;br&gt;• Knowledge of containerization and orchestration technologies such as Docker and Kubernetes.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with front-end frameworks such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.&lt;br&gt;• Familiarity with healthcare interoperability standards including HL7 and FHIR.&lt;br&gt;• Experience working in federal government or highly regulated environments.&lt;br&gt;• Know

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work location: Marietta, GA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Schedule: Full-time(day shift)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation range: $25/hr - $28/hr&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LTS&lt;/strong&gt; Health, a leader in healthcare kiosk production and deployment, seeks a dedicated and skilled &lt;strong&gt;Assembly Technician&lt;/strong&gt; to join our dynamic team in Marietta, GA. The ideal candidate will be a proactive self-starter with a passion for quality and a commitment to excellence. This role is crucial in assembling complex components to ensure each product meets our high standards of innovation and reliability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Perform Intricate Assembly Tasks: Utilize your advanced technical skills to assemble and integrate complex components and systems into our state-of-the-art healthcare kiosks.&lt;br&gt;• Collaborate for Improvement: Work closely with engineering and production leadership to enhance processes, solve issues, and drive continuous improvements, ensuring better efficiency and superior product quality.&lt;br&gt;• Champion Quality Assurance: Actively engage in quality assurance and continuous improvement initiatives, contributing innovative ideas and efforts to achieve excellence in all aspects of production.&lt;br&gt;• Conduct Thorough Inspections: Adhere to the highest quality standards by performing comprehensive inspections and implementing quality control measures, ensuring each product is dependable, efficient, and meets client requirements.&lt;br&gt;• Interpret Technical Specifications: Accurately interpret technical specifications, diagrams, and instructions for assembling intricate components and systems, ensuring precision in every task.&lt;br&gt;• Maintain Equipment Effectively: Perform regular maintenance and troubleshooting to minimize downtime and ensure a smooth production flow.&lt;br&gt;• Ensure Quality Control: Consistently conduct quality control checks to verify that products conform to specifications and quality standards.&lt;br&gt;• Utilize Specialized Tools: Skillfully use specialized hand and power tools to assemble and install components, including those requiring precision handling.&lt;br&gt;• Promote Safety and Cleanliness: Maintain a clean, orderly, and safe work environment, adhering to safety protocols and procedures to prevent accidents and injuries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• High school diploma or equivalent; a college degree is preferred.&lt;br&gt;• 3+ years of experience in manufacturing or assembly, with experience in handling complex components and systems.&lt;br&gt;• Proficiency with specialized hand and power tools, including precision tools.&lt;br&gt;• Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to train and mentor team members.&lt;br&gt;• Keen attention to detail and robust problem-solving skills.&lt;br&gt;• Ability to work both independently and collaboratively within a team.&lt;br&gt;• Physical stamina to stand for long periods and perform repetitive tasks.&lt;br&gt;• Flexibility to work varying hours and overtime as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice To Have:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Technical certification or vocational training in a related field.&lt;br&gt;• Experience with Lean Manufacturing principles and techniques.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s In It for You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• The Opportunity to support high-visibility federal missions&lt;br&gt;• A culture that values innovation, growth, and collaboration&lt;br&gt;• Access to cutting-edge tools and technologies&lt;br&gt;• Comprehensive benefits for you and your family&lt;br&gt;• A career path that rewards ambition and performance&lt;/p&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;United States - Remote&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Considerations:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;U.S. Citizen or Permanent Resident Required with the ability to obtain a Public Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Annual Salary Range:&lt;/strong&gt; 100K - 115K&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LTS&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is seeking a detail-oriented and collaborative &lt;strong&gt;Automation Team Analyst&lt;/strong&gt; to support the OMEGA program by identifying, analyzing, and documenting operational processes that can be improved or automated to enhance efficiency, consistency, and scalability across the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working under the direction of the Automation and AI Enablement Lead, in coordination with the Automation Engineer and Technology and Innovation Team, the Process Automation Analyst evaluates workflows across the COEs and program operations to identify automation opportunities in areas such as documentation management, release readiness, architecture governance, incident reporting, platform operations, and sustainment transitions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is responsible for developing reusable AI prompts, automation use cases, workflow templates, and prompt usage guidance that enable OMEGA teams to automate recurring operational activities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform Discovery and Workflow Analyis to include the following responsibilities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess existing workflows and identify manual, repetitive, and high-friction activities suitable for automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create Process maps and workflow analyses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft current-state and future-state workflow documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize automation use case inventory&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform Documentation and Process Automation Analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review program documentation, governance materials, process guidance, and operational artifacts to identify opportunities for summarization, standardization, and automation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document gap analysis summaries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend automation use cases for documentation automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare Workflow decision trees and business rules&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide Release Management and Governance Automation Support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the identification of automation opportunities related to release readiness, deployment risk review, architectural review preparation, and governance workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Release and governance workflow assessments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare Automation requirements for risk review and readiness analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide decision support criteria for governance checks&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform RCA and Incident Workflow Analysis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze incident response and root cause analysis workflows to identify opportunities for automation of summaries, draft artifacts, and operational reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare RCA workflow and artifact analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document incident reporting automation requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide recommendations for standardized RCA support processes&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Perform Automation Prompt Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop reusable AI prompts that enable automation of recurring operational tasks across the program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prompt templates for operational workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prompt documentation and usage guidance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributions to the centralized prompt library&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Role-specific prompt packs for COEs and operational teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;United States - Remote&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Considerations: &lt;/strong&gt;U.S. Citizen or Permanent Resident Required with the ability to obtain a Public Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Annual Salary Range:&lt;/strong&gt; 110K - 130K&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LTS &lt;/strong&gt;is seeking a detail-oriented and collaborative Automation Team Engineer to support the OMEGA program by designing, developing, implementing, and maintaining technical automation solutions. This helps to improve operational efficiency, reporting, decision support, and workflow execution across the program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working under the direction of the Automation and Innovation Lead and in coordination with the Process Automation Analyst, the Automation Engineer develops automation workflows, dashboards, integrations, reusable tooling, and technical solutions that support program automation initiatives across all COEs and the broader OMEGA program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role focuses on implementing scalable automation capabilities for operational processes such as documentation summarization, release risk analysis support, RCA draft generation support, reporting workflow automation, governance artifact processing, and sustainment transition support. While the Automation Engineer may automate report generation and reporting workflows, the design and development of analytics dashboards and value measurement reporting is performed by the Digital Value Analytics Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Through this role, the Automation Engineer will enable the OMEGA program to:&lt;br&gt;• Implement practical automation solutions that reduce manual effort&lt;br&gt;• Improve consistency and speed of recurring operational tasks&lt;br&gt;• Support more proactive release, governance, and incident workflows&lt;br&gt;• Enable automation of recurring dashboards, reports, and process checks&lt;br&gt;• Establish reusable automation assets that can scale across COEs and future workstreams&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Perform Automation Solution Development support:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain automation workflows and technical solutions that support priority automation initiatives across the program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop automation workflows and scripts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure automation solutions supporting operational processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft Technical documentation for implemented automations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support Reporting Workflow Automation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement automation capabilities that streamline recurring reporting processes and reduce manual effort associated with report generation and distribution across the program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate report generation and distribution workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create reusable templates and automation scripts supporting recurring operational reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft documentation of reporting workflow automation logic and configuration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Note: The Digital Value Analytics Team is responsible for designing analytics dashboards and defining program value metrics. The Automation Engineer focuses on automating the production and delivery of reports and operational data feeds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support Data Integration and Workflow Enablement:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate relevant program data sources, reporting systems, and operational artifacts to support automation solutions and decision-support workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data integrations supporting automation workflows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configured data pipelines and transformation logic&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Documentation of integrated systems and data flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide Release, Governance, and Incident Automation

